Love love love this recipe! My mama first introduced us to tapioca when we lived in Recife, north east of Brazil and it’s been my sister’s and my favorite! We do get creative and stuff many things in there 😋

Sweet version: add doce de leite
Savory version: spinach, cheese and tomato 

You can find the tapioca flour ready to use @hibrazil

@salvationarmyihq has an amazing couple of weeks coming up. Did you know about the thorough process to elect its General? It’s fascinating!

Growing up my friends would always ask if my parents worked for an airline because they always saw them in uniform. Sometimes I’d say yes 😂

As I grew up the questions were always an opportunity to share what my mom and dad lived for which has never been about their uniform. Jesus. The Salvation Army was the way they chose to serve Him and lead people to Him. 

Throughout 36 years (literally from the womb ha) I saw the Army inside and from the outside. Almost every state in Brazil and dozens of countries around the globe. I’ve seen it all and I have always been so proud of the “good apples” all around. 

 We are eating all the popcorn praying for God’s leading as they seat at the High Council 2023 and prayerfully make the right choice! 

Fun fact, reel cover bottom to top, my mama’s hat, grandma’s and great grandma’s 🤍

#salvationarmy #thesalvationarmy #highcouncil #highcouncil2023 #generalelection #exercitodesalvacao

About 13 years ago I learned from my cousin Becca about this diaper bag that truly was a dream come true. While living on the East Coast I saved and as a first time mama I finally bought one.

I came to California to visit Becca and researched the diaper bag brand only to find out their warehouse was on my way to Sta Barbara from LAX. I emailed them and to my surprise DeNai Jones, the head behind it and designer responded welcoming me in for a visit.

The day I arrived I was so excited and couldn’t believe I’d meet DeNai! My baby Julia got fussy, she gifted me a nursing cover, I nursed her and chatted for a few minutes.

Following year I sent DeNai a family Christmas card 🤪 this is how close she made me feel.

Years passed and Denai ventured on into this precise and darling craft of ceramics. Her shop is incredible and she has the gift of making anyone feel loved and seen.

DeNai is beautiful, can turn anything she touches into gold. A mother, wife, and one of a kind human being. I’m so lucky to know YOU! 

The mugs are a reminder to take the time to share my time intentionally with others, like you @d_e_n_a_i did with me, all those years ago!

Thank you. 

#ceramics #denaijones

We wanted to break our Africa trip on both ways to avoid the longest plane ride ever combined with a potential jet-legged that would cripple me from doing my best at all my business commitments in South Africa as well as as soon as we landed back in LA. And what a good choice (although I’m still jet-legged 😂) 

Frankfurt 🇩🇪 was pleasant, had the best charcuterie cheeses and meats from all over Europe. Every Uber and taxi was a Mercedes lol and we walked for 8 hs straight to enjoy our only day there 

I often think of not choosing the hardest options (new country, new language, more time traveling, and every single time the hardest choice is the best choice and I am full of gratitude for walking the soles of my feet into  every continent on the globe, because the memories to me are the people I hugged, the kids’ smiles my eyes saw, and the foods I ate.

When the hardest choice is the best choice, choose the hard. No short cuts will get us where we want to be 🤍

#entrepreneur #germany #frankfurt #jetlegged

How to have fun in Vegas as a family of 6, letssssssss go!

This one-pot meal from @rrayyme rrayyme is de-li-ci-oussssss and truly tastes better over the days. I’m chocked how easy it was to make and how amazing it tastes. 

✨Save to make later

Curry:
2 yellow onions sliced 1/2” pieces
2 carrots cut into 1” pieces
3 Yukon golden potatoes peeled and chopped 
1 tsp ginger grated
2 cloves of garlic minced
1/2 apple grated
1.5lbs skinless boneless chicken thighs cut into 1i. pieces
4 cups chicken broth
1 tbsp soy sauce
1 tbsp ketchup
1 package Japanese Curry Roux
Bowl of rice!

Caramelize the onion with oil in a heavy Dutch oven pot over medium heat. Next add garlic and ginger and cook chicken until no longer pink. Add chicken stock, apple, soy sauce and ketchup. Stir to mix then add carrot and potatoes. Simmer covered for 15 minutes and continue to cook until potato’s and carrots r softened. Turn off the heat and melt in the whole box of curry roux. Simmer for another 10-15 minutes and serve with a bowl of rice! ENJOY!
